====Noun====
'''ball'''  (''plural:'' '''[[balls]]''')
#<!--DefA-->A solid or hollow [[sphere]].
#<!--DefB-->An object, generally [[spherical]], used for playing games.
#<!--DefC-->A quantity of string, thread, etc, wound into a spherical shape.
#:''ball of wool''
#<!--DefD-->{{baseball}} A pitch that falls outside of the [[strike zone]].
#<!--DefE-->(''pinball'') An opportunity to launch the ball into play.
#<!--DefF-->(''ballistics'') A solid non-explosive missile for a cannon etc.
#<!--DefG-->(''mathematics'') The set of points in a [[metric space]] lying within a given distance (the [[radius]]) of a given point; specifically, the [[homologue]] of the [[disk]] in a [[Euclidean space]] of any number of [[dimension]]s.
#<!--DefH-->(''mildly vulgar slang''; ''usually in plural'') A [[testicle]].
#<!--DefI-->(''in plural''; ''mildly vulgar slang'') [[Nonsense]].
#:''That's a load of '''balls''', and you know it!'' - Synonyms - See [[WikiSaurus:Nonsense]]
#<!--DefJ-->(''slang'') [[Courage]].
#:''I doubt he’s got the '''balls''' to  tell him off.''
#<!--DefM-->{{cricket}} A single [[delivery]] by the [[bowler]], six of which make up an [[over]]

